  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "# Feature Issue\r\n\r\n### User Story\r\n\r\n>As I user\r\n>I want to know when notifications are loading\r\n>So that even in slower connection scenarios I know the app is working properly\r\n\r\n### Notes\r\n\r\n- Pull to refresh might not be necessary to implement, due to the fact that the AC state is already kept up-to-date using a polling strategy (see namespace `transport.message.core`).\r\n- Skeletons are probably the way to go, but this should be double-checked with the design team.\r\n- Animations are also open for design analysis, for example, when a new notification arrives and is inserted at the top.\r\n",
